    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-10-03T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-10-03T05:00:00-05:00" n="589"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/10–350: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Holmes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-10-03T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 3, 1950—11 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 3—5:35 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1934. Scott Foreign Office has just informed Embassy of receipt of telegram dated
                    October 3 from Peiping stating that on October 3 Foreign Minister Chou En-lai
                    called in Indian Ambassador Panikkar and informed him that if UN Armed Forces
                    crossed 38th parallel China would send troops across frontier participate in
                    defense North Korea. He said this action would not take place if only South
                    Koreans crossed parallel.</p>
                <p>Repeated <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> Moscow 67, <gloss
                        target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> New Delhi 46. Moscow’s 792, September 29 to
                    Department, repeated London 142, Delhi 39.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Holmes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
